# Manage Permissions Sheet

Display all **enabled modules**.

Each module should be displayed as an expandable section or card.

Example

Inventory

* Enable Module [Toggle]

Permissions

* View [Toggle]
* Create [Toggle]
* Update [Toggle]
* Delete [Toggle]
* Export [Toggle]

Sales

* Enable Module [Toggle]

Permissions

* View [Toggle]
* Create [Toggle]
* Update [Toggle]
* Delete [Toggle]

Reports

* Enable Module [Toggle]

Permissions

* View [Toggle]
* Export [Toggle]
* Print [Toggle]

## Module Toggle

Every module has an **Enable Module** toggle.

Rules:

* Turning ON grants the role access to the module.
* Turning OFF automatically disables every permission under that module.
* Permission toggles become disabled when the module is disabled.

## Permission Toggles

Display all **enabled permissions** from the Permissions page.

Each permission must have its own Toggle Switch.

Permission codes must be generated automatically using:

```text
{module.code}.{permission.code}
```

Example

Inventory Module

Enabled Permissions

* inventory.view
* inventory.create
* inventory.update
* inventory.export

Administrators must never manually enter permission codes.

## Saving

Clicking **Save** should:

* Save module access.
* Save permission assignments.
* Show a success toast notification.
* Changes should take effect immediately for newly authenticated sessions.

